        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 3:00PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 259 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers and isolated
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Gildford to 8 miles
northeast of Box Elder to near Parker School. Movement was northeast
at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Havre, Chinook, Azure, Parker School, Beaver Creek, Agency, St.
Pierre, Gildford, Sangrey, Boneau, Rocky Boy, Lohman, Laredo, Lloyd,
and Kremlin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
